350 function getUserAuth0Info(userDetails) {

351 var h = window.location.hostname,

352 base = 'https://' + h,

353 xhr = new XMLHttpRequest(),

354 method = 'GET';

355 xhr.responseType = 'json';

356 xhr.onload = function() {

357 var response = xhr.response || {},

358 auth0CustomerId = response.sub || '',

359 stripeCustomerId = '',

360 stripeSubscriptionStatus = '',

361 localStorageAuthProfile = localStorage.getItem('auth0:profile');

362

363 appMeta = response['http://nymag.com/app_metadata'] || localStorageAuthProfile && JSON.parse(localStorageAuthProfile)['http://nymag.com/app_metadata'];

364

365 if (appMeta && appMeta.stripe && appMeta.stripe.length) {

366 var longestSubDate = 0, longestSubDateIndex, longestSubDateCustomerIndex;

367

368 appMeta.stripe.forEach(function(customer, customerIndex) {

369 (customer.subscriptions || []).forEach(function(sub, subIndex) {

370 if (sub && sub.current_period_end >

371 longestSubDate) {

372 longestSubDate = sub.current_period_end;

373 longestSubDateIndex = subIndex;

374 longestSubDateCustomerIndex = customerIndex;

375 }

376 })

377 });

378

379 stripeCustomerId = appMeta.stripe[longestSubDateCustomerIndex].customer_id;

380 stripeSubscriptionStatus = appMeta.stripe[longestSubDateCustomerIndex].subscriptions[longestSubDateIndex].status;

381 }

382

383 userDetails.auth0_id = auth0CustomerId;

384 userDetails.stripe_customer_id = stripeCustomerId;

385 userDetails.stripe_subscription_status = stripeSubscriptionStatus;

386

387 loadPermutive(userDetails);

388 load(userDetails);

389 }

390 xhr.open(method, base + '/oauth/user/profile');

391 xhr.send();

392 };

394 function loadPermutive(userDetails) {

395 var u = {};

396 u.subAge = (function() {

397 var oldestDate, now = Date.now();

398 if (appMeta && appMeta.stripe && appMeta.stripe instanceof Array) {

399 appMeta.stripe.forEach(function(s){

400 (s.subscriptions || []).forEach(function(sub) {

401 if (sub && sub.current_period_start && (!oldestDate || sub.current_period_start < oldestDate)) oldestDate = sub.current_period_start;

402 })

403 });

404 }

405 if (oldestDate) {

406 return Math.floor((now/1000 - oldestDate) / 60 / 60 / 24);

407 }

408 return ''; // unset logged out users

409 })();

410 u.subStatus = !appMeta ? 'anonymous' : appMeta.has_subscription ? 'subscribed' : 'registered';

411 u.subInterval = (function () {

412 var activeSubPlanInterval = '';

413 if (appMeta && appMeta.stripe) {

414 appMeta.stripe.some(function (stripe) {

415 if (stripe.subscriptions) {

416 return stripe.subscriptions.some(function (sub) {

417 if (sub && sub.status === 'active' && sub.plan && sub.plan.interval) {

418 activeSubPlanInterval = sub.plan.interval;

419 return true;

420 }

421 });

422 }

423 });

424 }

425 return activeSubPlanInterval;

426 })();

427 u.subVia = (function(){

428 var arr = [];

429 if (appMeta) {

430 if (appMeta.has_pcd_subscription) arr.push('pcd');

431 if (appMeta.has_apple_subscription) arr.push('apple');

432 if (appMeta.has_google_subscription) arr.push('google');

433 if (appMeta.has_staff_subscription) arr.push('staff');

434 if (appMeta.has_giveaway_subscription) arr.push('giveaway');

435 }

436 return arr;

437 })();

438 u.newsletters = appMeta && appMeta.newsletter_subscriptions;

439 u.eventMember = appMeta && appMeta.newsletter_subscriptions && appMeta.newsletter_subscriptions.filter(function(x){return x==='Vulture Insider'||x==='TheCut Councin';});

440 u.isPrintSub = appMeta && appMeta.pcd_account_type === 'both';

441 window._nymPermutive = window._nymPermutive || {};

442 window._nymPermutive.user = {

443 newsletters: u.newsletters||null,

444 eventMember: u.eventMember||null,

445 isPrintSub: !!u.isPrintSub,

446 totalCount: userDetails.totalArticleCount||null,

447 standardCount: userDetails.standardArticleCount||null,

448 featureCount: userDetails.featureArticleCount||null,

449 magazineCount: userDetails.magazineArticleCount||null,

450 subStatus: u.subStatus||null,

451 subInterval: u.subInterval||null,

452 subVia: u.subVia||null,

453 subAge: u.subAge||null,

454 loyalty: userDetails.loyaltyLevel||null

455 };

456 permutive.addon('web', {page: window._nymPermutive});

457 }

459 function getUserLoyaltyLevel() {

460 var shortKey = 'c2',

461 visitDatesStr = localStorage.getItem('visitDates_' + shortKey) || '',

462 visitDates = visitDatesStr.split(','),

463 visitDatesLength = visitDates.length,

464 mostRecentVisit = visitDatesLength >

465 0 ? parseInt(visitDates[0], 10) : 0;

466

467 if (Date.now() - mostRecentVisit >

468 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000) {

469 visitDatesLength++;

470 }

471 if (visitDatesLength <= 1) {

472 return 'new';

473 } else if (visitDatesLength < 4) {

474 return 'return';

475 } else {

476 return 'loyal';

477 }

478 }

479 function toNumber(val) {

480 return parseInt(val, 10) || 0; // defaults to zero

481 }

482 function getNumberFromLocalStorage(key) {

483 return toNumber(localStorage.getItem(key)); // defaults to zero

484 }

485 function isNewVisit() {

486 var currentTimestamp = Date.now(),

487 sessionTTL = 1000 * 60 * 30, // keep session open for 30 minutes after last event

488 maxVisitDuration = 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24, // a visit can not last more than 24 hours

489 shortKey = 'c2',

490 previousActionTimestampKey = 'visitServicePreviousTimestamp_' + shortKey,

491 visitStartTimestampKey = 'visitServiceVisitStartTimestamp_' + shortKey,

492 // logic for the non-siteShortKey adaptation to be removed after 30 days

493 previousActionTimestamp = getNumberFromLocalStorage(previousActionTimestampKey),

494 sessionExpired = currentTimestamp - sessionTTL >

495 previousActionTimestamp,

496 // logic for the non-siteShortKey adaptation to be removed after 30 days

497 visitStartTimestamp = getNumberFromLocalStorage(visitStartTimestampKey),

498 visitDurationExpired = currentTimestamp - maxVisitDuration >

499 visitStartTimestamp;

500

501 return sessionExpired || visitDurationExpired;

502 }

503 function getUserVisitCount() {

504 var shortKey = 'c2',

505 // logic for the non-siteShortKey adaptation to be removed after 30 days

506 visitCount = getNumberFromLocalStorage('visitServiceCount_' + shortKey) || 1;

507

508 if (isNewVisit()) {

509 visitCount++;

510 }

511

512 return visitCount;

513 }

2334

2335 <p class="clay-paragraph" data-editable="text" data-uri="www.thecut.com/_components/clay-paragraph/instances/ckhmbdc4n000j6ln3fqdbxswd@published" data-word-count="88">

2336With states like Oregon decriminalizing small amounts of illegal drugs and legalizing psilocybin, you could say the true winner of the 2020 election <a href="https://www.thecut.com/2020/11/weed-and-mushrooms-win-legalization-in-election-2020-results.html">

2337was drugs</a>

2338. And nothing won bigger than cannabis. New Jersey, Arizona, South Dakota, and Montana have approved it for recreational use, while Mississippi will be offering it for certain medical conditions. Right now, you’re more likely to live in a state that has some form of legalized cannabis than not. And even if you can’t get weed, hemp-based CBD is readily available across the country.</p>

2339

2340

2341 <p class="clay-paragraph" data-editable="text" data-uri="www.thecut.com/_components/clay-paragraph/instances/ckhmbgohd000u3h6aidje8ik4@published" data-word-count="65">

2342But if you’re new to all this, it can be confusing. What’s the difference between hemp-derived CBD and marijuana-derived CBD? If you live in a state where cannabis is available recreationally like Massachusetts, does that mean your friend in California can ship you some weed? And on a much more basic level: What should you buy to deal with all the stress of this year?</p>

2343

2344

2345 <p class="clay-paragraph" data-editable="text" data-uri="www.thecut.com/_components/clay-paragraph/instances/ckhmbjbk600103h6anzhz13oa@published" data-word-count="57">

2346First, hemp-derived CBD is simply much easier to find. It’s legal across the country because it contains less than 0.3 percent THC, which is the compound in cannabis that’s psychoactive. That’s not to say it won’t affect you. If you’re using it to relax or fall asleep, it’s effective — it’s just not quite like being high.</p>

2347

2348

2349 <p class="clay-paragraph" data-editable="text" data-uri="www.thecut.com/_components/clay-paragraph/instances/ckhmbm0dr00163h6aitcvwcwu@published" data-word-count="55">

2350As for the second question: No, you can’t get a friend to ship across state lines. That’s still illegal. Every state grows and produces its own THC-based products, and state laws about what’s legal and illegal are complicated. For example, in California, anything goes, while in New York you can only get vapes and tinctures.</p>

2351

2352

2353 <p class="clay-paragraph" data-editable="text" data-uri="www.thecut.com/_components/clay-paragraph/instances/ckhmbqqic001c3h6avvkhme18@published" data-word-count="73">

2354With that in mind, we tried to simplify things in our shopping guide. Below are some suggestions for hemp CBD-based gifts that can be shipped anywhere in the country and are great for beginners and advanced users alike. And if you do want to get something for the stoner in your life who really knows their weed, we also included a few items they can use while smoking or making their own edibles.</p>

9807'use strict';

9808/**

9809 * mount legacy services from _global.js, if any

9810 */

9811

9812function mountLegacyServices() {

9813 Object.keys(window.modules).filter(key =>

9814 typeof key === 'string' && key.match(/\.legacy$/)).forEach(key =>

9815 window.require(key));

9816}

9817

9818function tryToMount(fn, el, name) {

9819 try {

9820 fn(el); // init the controller

9821 } catch (e) {

9822 const elementTag = el.outerHTML.slice(0, el.outerHTML.indexOf(el.innerHTML));

9823 console.error(`Error initializing controller for "${name}" on "${elementTag}"`, e);

9824 }

9825}

9826/**

9827 * mount client.js component controllers

9828 */

9829

9830

9831function mountComponentModules() {

9832 Object.keys(window.modules).filter(key =>

9833 typeof key === 'string' && key.match(/\.client$/)).forEach(key =>

9834 {

9835 let controllerFn = window.require(key);

9836

9837 if (typeof controllerFn === 'function') {

9838 const name = key.replace('.client', ''),

9839 instancesSelector = `[data-uri*="_components/${name}/"]`,

9840 defaultSelector = `[data-uri$="_components${name}"]`,

9841 instances = document.querySelectorAll(instancesSelector),

9842 defaults = document.querySelectorAll(defaultSelector);

9843

9844 for (let el of instances) {

9845 tryToMount(controllerFn, el, name);

9846 }

9847

9848 for (let el of defaults) {

9849 tryToMount(controllerFn, el, name);

9850 }

9851 }

9852 });

9853} // Make sure that a `window.process.env.NODE_ENV` is available in the client for any dependencies,

9854// services, or components that could require it

9855// note: the `` value is swapped for the actual environment variable in /lib/cmd/compile/scripts.js

9856

9857

9858window.process = window.process || {};

9859window.process.env = window.process.env || {};

9860

9861if (!window.process.env.NODE_ENV) {

9862 window.process.env.NODE_ENV = '';

9863} // note: legacy controllers that require legacy services (e.g. dollar-slice) must

9864// wait for DOMContentLoaded to initialize themselves, as the files themselves must be mounted first

9865

9866

9867mountLegacyServices();

9868mountComponentModules();

9869 // ]]

9870 </script>

9871</body>

9872

9873</html>
